# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# reception-consent-policy.form — first-encounter consent across ALL
#                                 channels, as a phase-mobile policy cell
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# A hard-coded default (consentFindable = false baked into a carrier's code) is
# dead ice: frozen by force, sitting OUTSIDE the body's metabolism, unable to
# flow, re-tune, or be queried. This holds the same decision as a POLICY the
# body HOLDS — a Recipe (substance) that can rest at any STATE (ice / water /
# gas) and move between them WHEN WE CHOOSE.
#
#   SUBSTANCE  Recipe — "how first-encounter consent is decided" (kind, conserved).
#   STATE      ours to set, and to move by hand:
#     ice    — frozen as the stable default a carrier reads (today's resting state)
#     water  — reopened (MELT) to re-tune a facet or the rule, then re-FREEZE
#     gas    — interned as potential, queryable by shape, barely instantiated
#   MELT/FREEZE are DELIBERATE — "if we choose to" — not count-driven. The
#   NodeID and the kind are conserved across every move; only the state shifts.
#
# ONE policy over EVERY channel's first encounter (the matrix in
# first-encounter-protocol.form: agent<->agent, human<->body, ...). The
# universal rule is shared; each channel carries its consents as a FACET —
# data, not a parallel hard-coding.
#
# Ported from the sibling product repo (Coherence-Network), where each facet
# below is projected onto a live carrier (a web form, a coordination script).
# Those carriers are named honestly here as living in that repo, not this
# one — this kernel holds the RULE (`form-stdlib/reception-consent.fk`,
# below), never the carrier that reads it.

(reception-consent-policy

  (lineage
    (substance     Recipe)                               # how first-encounter consent is decided
    (runnable-heart form-stdlib/reception-consent.fk)    # the RULE in Form, four-way proven (reception-consent-band)
    (realizes      first-encounter-protocol.form consent))  # the (consent open) for every pairing

  # ── The universal rule (every channel, every facet) ─────────────────
  # Each consent is OPEN to the arriving cell. A default is only the resting
  # position a carrier shows; the arriving cell sets the true value. Exposure-
  # bearing consents rest CLOSED — no silent exposure; nothing records, names,
  # enrolls, or remembers a cell that only came to witness.
  (rule
    (terms-belong-to  the-arriving-cell)                 # the default is a resting position, not a verdict
    (exposure-bearing rest-closed)                       # findable, email, enroll, record-relation, remember — opt-in only
    (witness-default  no-record-no-name-no-enroll)       # met != engaged; engagement waits for a yes
    (revocable        always)
    (silence          keeps-the-rest-state))             # not answering leaves the resting default

  # ── The facets — one per channel, each its consents + resting states ─
  # Carried as DATA: a new channel drops in a facet; the rule and the phase
  # machinery are shared. open = rests yes (visible, revocable); closed = rests
  # no (opt-in).
  (facets
    (web-begin                                           # human <-> body, a contributor door — carrier lives in Coherence-Network
      (share-name open) (findable closed) (email-updates closed)
      (carrier not-present-in-this-kernel-by-design))     # MANIFEST.md keeps web/API out of this repo

    (agent                                               # agent <-> agent / agent <-> body
      (recorded-as-relation closed)                      # a sibling who only reads the thread is not recorded
      (carrier this-repo:AGENTS.md-session-embodiment))

    (body-arrival                                        # the session-start recognition of an arriving cell
      (relationship-memory closed-until-allowed)         # recorded only when remembering is on
      (carrier form-stdlib/arrival.fk)))                 # the Form-native welcome; persistence stays carrier-pending

  # ── State moves (deliberate — "if we choose to"), available in EVERY facet
  (states
    (ice    (frozen-default carrier-reads)               # the resting state today
            (projection     per-carrier))
    (water  (melt   -> re-tune (a facet OR the rule))
            (freeze -> ice))
    (gas    (interned queryable)))                       # the policy as potential, asked by shape

  # ── Why one policy over all channels, not a hard-coding per door ────
  # A baked-in literal is one carrier's private frozen copy — invisible as a
  # decision, un-meltable, un-queryable, drifting the moment a second door bakes
  # its own. ONE held policy with per-channel facets means: tune a facet once
  # (melt), refreeze, and that channel's door shows the new resting state; the
  # rule changes once and every channel follows.
  (invariant
    (one-policy               every-channel)
    (facet-is-data            not-parallel-hard-coding)
    (phase-by-choice          not-by-force)
    (carrier-reads-projection never-bakes-its-own)))
